# Front-end architecture document

The canonical structural overview is **`front-end/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`**.

When your edits affect **any** of the following, **update that file in the same change** (or immediately after in the same task):

- Provider order or composition in `App.tsx` / `main.tsx`
- New, removed, or renamed global context providers under `contexts/`
- Routing: public vs protected layout, new top-level routes, or `Layout` responsibilities
- New or reorganized API surface in `services/api.ts` (or a new service module pattern)
- Socket connection contract or how features subscribe (document-level change only if behavior or ownership shifts)
- New top-level `src/` directories with a defined architectural role

If the change is purely local to one component with no boundary impact, no doc update is required.

Do not duplicate the full coding-style checklist here; keep **`frontend-architecture.mdc`** as the convention source and **`ARCHITECTURE.md`** as the map of the system.
